---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MedicalDisclaimer from '../../components/MedicalDisclaimer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Retatrutide Dosing Guide: Starting Dose, Titration & Maintenance (2026)"
  description="Complete retatrutide dosing schedule based on clinical trials. Learn the starting dose, titration plan, and maintenance dosing for optimal weight loss."
>
  <style>
    .hero { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #059669 100%); color: white; padding: 80px 24px 60px; text-align: center; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.2; }
    .content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 60px 24px 120px; }
    .content h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 48px 0 16px; }
    .content p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .content table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 24px 0; }
    .content th { background: #f9fafb; padding: 12px; text-align: left; border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb; }
    .content td { padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb; }
  </style>

  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Retatrutide Dosing Guide</h1>
    <p>Starting dose, titration schedule, and maintenance dosing based on Phase 2/3 clinical trials.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h2>Standard Retatrutide Titration Schedule</h2>
    <p>Based on Phase 2 clinical trial protocol (likely to be the FDA-approved schedule):</p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Weeks</th>
          <th>Weekly Dose</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>1-4</td>
          <td>0.5 mg</td>
          <td>Initial dose - assess tolerance</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>5-8</td>
          <td>1 mg</td>
          <td>First dose increase</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>9-12</td>
          <td>2 mg</td>
          <td>Continue titration</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>13-16</td>
          <td>4 mg</td>
          <td>Moderate dose</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>17-20</td>
          <td>8 mg</td>
          <td>Higher dose for more weight loss</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>21+</td>
          <td>12 mg</td>
          <td><strong>Maximum maintenance dose</strong></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Why Slow Titration Matters</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Reduces side effects:</strong> Nausea and GI issues are MUCH worse if you start too high or increase too fast</li>
      <li><strong>Better tolerance:</strong> Body adapts gradually to medication</li>
      <li><strong>Lower dropout rates:</strong> Clinical trials show people who titrate slowly are more likely to stay on medication</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What Dose Gives the Most Weight Loss?</h2>
    <p><strong>12 mg weekly:</strong> Maximum dose, 24.2% average weight loss (Phase 2)</p>
    <p><strong>8 mg weekly:</strong> 22.8% average weight loss</p>
    <p><strong>4 mg weekly:</strong> 17.3% average weight loss</p>

    <p><strong>More is better, but not everyone needs 12mg.</strong> Your provider will determine the optimal dose based on your response and tolerability.</p>

    <h2>Can You Skip Doses or Speed Up Titration?</h2>
    <p><strong>Don't skip doses:</strong> Weekly injections must be consistent for optimal results.</p>
    <p><strong>Don't speed up titration:</strong> Increasing too fast = severe nausea and higher dropout risk.</p>
    <p><strong>Missed dose?</strong> Take within 3 days. If more than 3 days late, skip and resume normal schedule.</p>

    <h2>Maintenance Dosing: How Long Do You Stay On Retatrutide?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Weight loss phase:</strong> 48-72 weeks to reach maximum weight loss</li>
      <li><strong>Maintenance phase:</strong> Most people stay on retatrutide indefinitely to maintain weight loss</li>
      <li><strong>What happens if you stop?</strong> Weight regain is common (60-70% regain within 1-2 years)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Injection Technique</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Site:</strong> Abdomen, thigh, or upper arm</li>
      <li><strong>Rotate sites:</strong> Don't inject in the same spot weekly</li>
      <li><strong>Timing:</strong> Can be taken any time of day, with or without food</li>
      <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Refrigerate until first use, then can be kept at room temp for 21 days</li>
    </ul>

    <MedicalDisclaimer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
